-- PRESS DIGEST - China - June 23
-- By Chen Yixin and Fayen Wong
-- Sun Jun 22, 2014 09:32PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, June 23 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Monday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

CHINA SECURITIES JOURNAL - Xuan Changneng, a senior official of the People's Bank of China, said the country must roll out a deposit insurance system which is vitally important to its financial stability.  SHANGHAI SECURITIES NEWS - Four Chinese brokerages - Guotai Junan Securities Co Ltd, Orient Securities Co, Shenyin & Wanguo Securities Co and Great Wall Securities Co - have received regulatory approval to act as the first batch of market makers in the country's nascent over-the-counter equity market.  SECURITIES TIMES - Starting on Monday, the number of brokerages allowed to borrow stocks from institutions more than doubled to 73 from 30, making it easier for investors to short shares in China's stock markets.  CHINA DAILY  - More lawyers will be encouraged to serve as legal advisers for government agencies to help ensure that officials' decisions are legal, a senior justice ministry official said.